
Project Overview
This document outlines the 3-sprint breakdown for the Nestlé Order Management System (OMS), a mobile and web platform connecting retailers, distributors, and administrators. The system enables end-to-end order placement, fulfillment, tracking, and analytics.

Sprint Summary
Sprint	Focus	Story Points	Duration
Sprint 1	Authentication & Core Retailer Features	34 pts	Weeks 1–2
Sprint 2	Order Management & Distributor Functions	38 pts	Weeks 3–4
Sprint 3	Admin Dashboard, Analytics & Polish	30 pts	Weeks 5–6

Sprint Rationale
The three sprints follow a layered delivery approach:
Sprint 1 establishes the foundation — user onboarding, login security, and the core product-browsing and ordering experience for retailers.
Sprint 2 builds the operational layer — distributor workflows, order approvals, delivery tracking, and real-time stock visibility.
Sprint 3 delivers the intelligence layer — admin analytics, reporting, promotional tools, and system-wide polishing.

Sprint 1 — Foundation & Retailer Core
Weeks 1–2  (2-week sprint)
